- SSH Daemon Config File is located at /etc/ssh/sshd_config
- ls lah gives human readable file size
- to rerun certain history command do !47 and it'll run 47th command from history
- to display current server distribution: lsb_release -a 
- Linux info: uname -a
- 64bit or 32bit: uname -i

- File system human readable df -h
- Free memory or ram: free -mh

- get a nicer version of top: sudo apt-get install -y htop
- in htop, press f4 to search/filter/kill processes
